sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K325100
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description:
EPIC Firefly Luciferase and LRE
P. Pyralis
(E. coli optimised)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a mutant luciferase that is very much brighter than wild-type. It is supplied in an operon with an enzyme (LRE) that regenerates its substrate. When supplied with luciferin and placed under a promoter it will emit light at a green wavelength. If D-cysteine is added the LRE will be able to regenerate the luciferin substrate.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ben Reeve and Paul Masset
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Codon optimised and synthesised by DNA 2.0
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It was ensured that no unwanted restriction sites were created during optimisation. A BamH1 site was added between the two genes.
